15/01/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek Police said Friday (13 January) that they have smashed a human trafficking attempt in the country's northeast. According to the police, two Greek citizens were seized while transporting 80 illegal migrants from Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Iraq, Nigeria and Pakistan in a hidden compartment of a truck. The action took place in the region of Evros, at the border with Turkey. (Kathimerini - 14/01/06) 
